headline: E-Commerce Stocks Have Recovered From Tariff Hit. What To Watch From Amazon, eBay Earnings.
summary: Amazon stock and other e-commerce players eBay and Etsy have momentum heading into second-quarter earnings season as fears about tariffs ease.  In a note previewing Q2 earnings season, Bernstein analysts led by Nikhil Devnani raised their price targets for shares of eBay and Etsy, while reiterating a 235 price target and "top pick" designation for Amazon stock.

headline: Bernstein on U.S. internet stocks: Will the optimism last?
summary: Investing.com -- U.S. internet stocks have rallied strongly heading into second-quarter earnings, helped by modest improvements in gross merchandise volume (GMV) growth and favourable currency movements, according to Bernstein. But the outlook remains uncertain.
